# tpxo2bdy repository
#
# by
# AC Goglio - CMCC
# annachiara.goglio@cmcc.it
#
# The aim of this code is to build tidal boundary files for EAS system
#
# HOW TO COMPILE THE CODE AND RUN IT 
#
# 1) Load the comp environment (ONLY the first time you run the code)
# module load intel19.5/19.5.281 impi19.5/19.5.281 impi19.5/netcdf/C_4.7.2-F_4.5.2_CXX_4.3.1
# 
# 2) Compile the code (ONLY the first time you run the code)
# ifort -o extract_tidalbdy_txt -O2 extract_HC_txt.f90 subs.f90 ${FFLAGS} ${LDFLAGS}
#
# 3) Load the py env
# module load anaconda
# source activate %your-virtual-env%
#
# 4) run the whole procedure
# sh run_bdy_txt.sh 
#
# 5) To check the outputs (and compare them to another tidal bdy dataset) 
#    set (following comments in the code) and run the script
#    tpxoVsfes.py
